^b@2^*BMarty Bergen: ^*N|cp||at|Every bridge player must know whether his partner's bid is forcing. In my experience, many players are deficient in this area. Can you prove me wrong? For each example, state whether or not the last bid is forcing. Assume standard bidding. |
PG| ***** 1 ***** |


NT||
%%%%%%%%%%% Example 1
qx||CS|6|fp|2|AT|^-
{      Forcing or Not - Example 1    }
^-|
ht|d|cs|6|at|^B{|ia|,1Hp1Sp2C|at|}|hf|k|lb|*yIs this bid forcing^^n|
ht|l|cp|8|AT|
^b@2^*BMarty Bergen: ^*N|cp||at|Not forcing. If opener had wanted to force, he could have jump shifted to 3@C. Responder would not want to find a second bid holding:|ht|o|CS|6|at|^o{|ih|psSQ876 H9 DA8765 C43|at|}|
PG| ***** 3 ***** |


NT||

